[{"question":"And the motivation appears to be financial, is that right?","answer":"Yes, I think you\u0027re right.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":34,"aSentId":35},{"question":"Can you tell me what your reaction is to this shocking story?","answer":"Well, I know, you know, how it was down there because I was there quite a bit.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":43,"aSentId":44},{"question":"So when you say lies, I mean -- when you say lies, are you disputing that your son along with the other suspects kept this woman who is, we know, mentally disabled and her child captive for two years?","answer":"Yes, that\u0027s wrong.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":48,"aSentId":49},{"question":"What is wrong about it?","answer":"What is -- everything is wrong about it.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":53,"aSentId":54},{"question":"So are you saying that absolutely none of this is true?","answer":"Absolutely none of this is true, no.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":59,"aSentId":60},{"question":"Excuse me?","answer":"No, after you.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":63,"aSentId":64},{"question":"What was that?","answer":"No, you say what you want to say, Becky.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":65,"aSentId":66},{"question":"If none of this happened, why are the police taking this dramatic action of charging your son and his partner and the third person and potentially a fourth with extremely serious offenses?","answer":"Because Jordie and Jessie heard the little girl crying a lot in the bedroom that they were at.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":68,"aSentId":69},{"question":"ORGAN: Who was taking her money that she was getting for her disability?","answer":"She was giving them a couple of hundred dollars a month for staying there and she was getting her own food.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":75,"aSentId":76},{"question":"Have you spoken to your son Jordie about this since he was charged?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":80,"aSentId":81},{"question":"And what does he say?","answer":"He\u0027s devastated that all this is being said about them.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":82,"aSentId":83},{"question":"You say that you -- you have had this woman and her daughter at your house in the last two years several times, is that right?","answer":"Yes, yes, I have.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":91,"aSentId":92},{"question":"And she gave no suggestion to you that she was being held captive or being abused in any way?","answer":"No.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":93,"aSentId":94},{"question":"Did you have any way of -- did you have any way of proving that she was at your house?","answer":"Yes, I do.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":96,"aSentId":97},{"question":"How would you prove it?","answer":"I\u0027ve got plenty of pictures proving it.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":98,"aSentId":99},{"question":"Of this woman in the last two years inside your property?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":100,"aSentId":101},{"question":"So you believe that your son and the other suspects who have been charged are being framed and that this woman herself has been guilty of abusing her child, is that your position?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":102,"aSentId":103},{"question":"It doesn\u0027t make much sense to me that the police would simply believe her word against three other people if, as you say, there has been absolutely no abuse whatsoever?","answer":"Well, you know, this is a little town of Ashland, and they do know Jordie and they know Jess and they are just trying to make a big case out of what Shannon did.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":105,"aSentId":106},{"question":"Did you at any point think that this T-shirt would breech any of the school\u0027s regulations?","answer":"No, because we knew that there wouldn\u0027t be an issue, you know, especially and particularly here in southern West Virginia where we\u0027re primarily -- I mean, basically we are a gun culture here.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":128,"aSentId":129},{"question":"Would it not be best to have the debate about gun control and guns and the NRA out of school classrooms and school playgrounds?","answer":"Well, you may have an argument there in certain places, Piers.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":194,"aSentId":195},{"question":"How damaging is this to the national security of the American people that this trust was violated?","answer":"I think it was irreversible and significant damage to this nation.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":216,"aSentId":217},{"question":"Has this helped America\u0027s enemies?","answer":"I believe it has, and I believe it will hurt us and our allies.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":218,"aSentId":219},{"question":"What is your reaction to that?","answer":"This is what the government says in every single case whenever somebody exposes what they want to hide from the people over whom they\u0027re ruling.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":229,"aSentId":230},{"question":"So when they say that more than 50 plots globally have been thwarted as a direct result of all this surveillance, are they lying?","answer":"No, it\u0027s not that they are lying.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":237,"aSentId":238},{"question":"Because I think the key question now is what is the line and who draws it?","answer":"Look, I had clearances for communications intelligence for years in the government.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":248,"aSentId":249},{"question":"You weren\u0027t -- but the charges were dropped, right?","answer":"They were dropped because the president was, among other things, conducting warrantless wiretapping on which I was overheard and lying about it, by the way.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":274,"aSentId":275},{"question":"Should Edward Snowden have stayed in America?","answer":"No, I think - first, I think he\u0027s benefited very much -- he\u0027s benefited.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":282,"aSentId":283},{"question":"What is your reaction to his tragic death?","answer":"I mean, it\u0027s --","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":322,"aSentId":323},{"question":"Are you speaking to me?","answer":"Unspeakably horrible.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":324,"aSentId":325},{"question":"Do you think we could find a way in?","answer":"I don\u0027t know.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":360,"aSentId":361},{"question":"Paris, how the devil are you?","answer":"Good.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":370,"aSentId":371},{"question":"Has that to make you change the way you behave on Twitter and so on?","answer":"Definitely, because, you know, this could not have happened, you know, five or 10 years ago.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":386,"aSentId":387},{"question":"They tried to take your dog, didn\u0027t they?","answer":"Yes, they actually tried to take my dog, which --","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":389,"aSentId":390},{"question":"How did you find her?","answer":"I love Sofia.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":401,"aSentId":402},{"question":"Can you horrify my viewers now and tell them how much the last fragrance 16th, Dazzle, how much it took in sales?","answer":"All my fragrances are over $1.5 billion so far.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":417,"aSentId":418},{"question":"And you\u0027re not married yet, are you?","answer":"No.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":424,"aSentId":425},{"question":"Do you, Piers Morgan, take Paris Hilton to be your wedded wife?","answer":"I do.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":429,"aSentId":430},{"question":"And do you, Paris Hilton, take Piers Morgan to be your lawful wedded husband?","answer":"I do.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":431,"aSentId":432},{"question":"Is that right?","answer":"I call him my man.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":447,"aSentId":448},{"question":"Is he a man yet?","answer":"Yes, he\u0027s very mature.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":449,"aSentId":450},{"question":"Is he aware that I exist as your only husband to date?","answer":"He\u0027s very aware of that.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":451,"aSentId":452},{"question":"How is he dealing of that?","answer":"Of course, he\u0027s a little bit jealous of you.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":453,"aSentId":454},{"question":"Do you think you may see any wedding bells with River?","answer":"You know, we just celebrated our one-year anniversary and I\u0027ve never been happier.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":456,"aSentId":457},{"question":"What the hell is going on?","answer":"Well, you know, that\u0027s bad news for him.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":486,"aSentId":487},{"question":"All this stuff recently just seems to be nibbling away at the fact that he was Mr. Transparent and now he\u0027s Mr. Sneaky?","answer":"Look, I mean, the minute that you are mentioning in the same sentence as Dick Cheney when your campaign slogan was hope and change, I think you\u0027re in a very problematic position and you mentioned the word trust, and I think that that is the one word that describes where he is right now.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":511,"aSentId":512},{"question":"Is he losing the people that really, really put the money up and backed him?","answer":"I don\u0027t think so.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":521,"aSentId":522},{"question":"But isn\u0027t this the point?","answer":"We\u0027re not spied on but their conversations are --","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":531,"aSentId":532},{"question":"Isn\u0027t that the difference?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":534,"aSentId":535},{"question":"Brand experience?","answer":"Brand.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":546,"aSentId":547},{"question":"I mean, they went as if they couldn\u0027t understand a word he was saying?","answer":"Piers --","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":563,"aSentId":564},{"question":"Why would she use that analogy, do you think?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t know.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":583,"aSentId":584},{"question":"Would Rasputin divorce his wife by text?","answer":"I love Russell Brand.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":596,"aSentId":597},{"question":"Van Jones, I mean, can you ever imagine being in the position where you would divorce somebody by text message?","answer":"Well, I can\u0027t imagine -- people do a lot of stuff by text messaging.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":610,"aSentId":611},{"question":"Really?","answer":"There -- I mean, there are -- you know, it\u0027s interesting that technological advancements have done so many great things, but I think we\u0027ve lost the intimacy of having these sorts of conversations and it allows people, especially young people, to have an excuse to not talk about awkward things that can be very uncomfortable like this, like a divorce.","docId":"130618pmt","qSentId":616,"aSentId":617}]